metadata.song: A Rush Of Blood To The Head
metadata.editComments: Just changed Cmaj7/E to Em7. Almost all tabs have this chord marked and I hear the D (m7) and not the C (b6) on the chord.

metadata.song: A Rush Of Blood To The Head
metadata.editComments: I reanalyzed the Chorus as being a key change to F Major instead of sticking to Am. It doesn't make a lot of sense to have a part with no Am being in A minor. F Lydian could have been an option, but it would have made both D7 (II) and Bbmaj7 (bVII) non diatonic, so I chose F Major so that only D7 (VI) would be non diatonic.

metadata.song: A Rush Of Blood To The Head
metadata.editComments: this whole bridge is a Fmaj chord.  I'm not sure what the two chords are, but theres an A in the first chord and it moves down to G on the second.  This was the closest representation I could do.
